`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- The test suite is already comprehensive (37 tests > the 6 required), covering all 6 templates, determinism, context validity, and QuestDef structure.
- The `makeRng([0, 0, 0])` helper pattern uses the controlled-RNG approach — wrapping to avoid `undefined` on short arrays. This is the right way to test pool-based selection without involving the real `scopedRNG`.
- `buildQuestContext` consuming exactly 3 RNG values regardless of category is a deliberate design choice to prevent PRNG stream drift between categories — worth noting as a pattern when building similar procedural generators.
